BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260322T200000Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20260322T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for the April Capital Region Mesh meetup featuring a hands-on Mesh Open House and a presentation on emerging LoRa 2.4 GHz voice capabilities in Meshtastic.\n\nLocation: Kent Thomas Room at the Unitarian Universalist Church, 274 Pleasant Street, Concord. Google Maps: https://maps.app.goo.gl/1dg2gf1RueUyXagJ7 (Enter through the East entrance; someone will be there to greet you.)\n\nTime: 7:00–9:00 PM (Space is limited — please RSVP to events@capitalmesh.net)\n\nAgenda: • 7:00–7:15 — Arrivals & Introductions • 7:15–8:00 — Mesh Open House • 8:00–8:10 — Break / Open Conversation • 8:10–8:40 — Experiments with LoRa Voice • 8:40–9:00 — Working Session\n\nMesh Open House: Bring a device or learn with one of ours. Volunteers will help you flash firmware, configure radios, join MeshCore rooms, and get fully onboarded.\n\nExperiments with LoRa Voice: Explore emerging digital voice capabilities over LoRa 2.4 GHz, including experimental codecs, hardware considerations, and early prototypes.\n\nWorking Session: Identify testing opportunities, volunteer roles, and next steps for spring deployments.\n\nWhether you're returning or joining for the first time, you’re welcome to attend any portion of the evening.
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260401T210000
